<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Case File #114</title>
  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#070707;
      --panel:#101010;
      --panel-2:#151515;
      --line:#2a2a2a;
      --soft:#8b8b8b;
      --text:#d0d0d0;
      --white:#f1f1f1;
      --red:#8b0000;
      --red-soft:#ffcccc;
      --gold:#c9a84c;
      --green:#7CFC98;
    }

    *{
      box-sizing:border-box;
      -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
    }

    html{
      scroll-behavior:smooth;
    }

    body{
      margin:0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(139,0,0,0.12), transparent 30%),
        repeating-linear-gradient(
          to bottom,
          rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 0px,
          rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px,
          transparent 2px,
          transparent 4px
        ),
        var(--bg);
      color:var(--text);
      font-family:"Courier New", Courier, monospace;
      line-height:1.75;
      padding:12px;
    }

    .file{
      width:100%;
      max-width:880px;
      margin:0 auto;
      background:linear-gradient(180deg,#111111,#0d0d0d);
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      box-shadow:
        0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.02) inset,
        0 16px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
      overflow:hidden;
      position:relative;
    }

    .file::before{
      content:"INTERNAL AFFAIRS";
      position:absolute;
      top:26px;
      right:-42px;
      transform:rotate(28deg);
      border:2px solid rgba(139,0,0,0.28);
      color:rgba(255,140,140,0.12);
      padding:6px 22px;
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:3px;
      pointer-events:none;
    }

    .topbar{
      background:#181818;
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:14px 16px;
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:8px;
      align-items:center;
    }

    .badge{
      display:inline-block;
      background:var(--red);
      color:var(--red-soft);
      padding:4px 10px;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      border-radius:2px;
    }

    .topmeta{
      color:#909090;
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:1.2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      line-height:1.5;
    }

    .content{
      padding:20px 16px 28px;
    }

    .header-grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr;
      gap:14px;
    }

    .section-tag{
      color:#656565;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:3px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:8px;
    }

    .title{
      margin:0 0 10px;
      color:var(--white);
      font-size:24px;
      font-weight:normal;
      letter-spacing:1.5px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      line-height:1.3;
    }

    .subtitle{
      color:#9a9a9a;
      font-size:12px;
      letter-spacing:1px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:14px;
      line-height:1.6;
    }

    .stamp{
      display:inline-block;
      border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.45);
      color:rgba(201,168,76,0.9);
      padding:5px 10px;
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      transform:rotate(-2deg);
      margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    .meta-box{
      background:var(--panel-2);
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:12px;
    }

    .meta-row{
      padding:8px 0;
      border-bottom:1px solid #242424;
    }

    .meta-row:last-child{
      border-bottom:none;
    }

    .meta-label{
      display:block;
      color:#777;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:4px;
    }

    .meta-value{
      color:#e4e4e4;
      font-size:14px;
      line-height:1.6;
    }

    .divider{
      border:none;
      border-top:1px solid var(--line);
      margin:22px 0;
    }

    .section{
      margin-bottom:26px;
    }

    h2{
      margin:0 0 12px;
      color:var(--white);
      font-size:18px;
      font-weight:normal;
      letter-spacing:1px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      line-height:1.4;
    }

    p{
      margin:0 0 14px;
      color:#b9b9b9;
      font-size:14px;
    }

    strong{
      color:#eeeeee;
      font-weight:normal;
    }

    .list{
      display:grid;
      gap:8px;
      margin:12px 0 14px;
    }

    .list div{
      position:relative;
      padding-left:18px;
      color:#b5b5b5;
      font-size:14px;
      line-height:1.65;
    }

    .list div::before{
      content:"▸";
      position:absolute;
      left:0;
      color:var(--red);
    }

    .quote{
      margin:16px 0 18px 8px;
      padding:10px 12px;
      border-left:2px solid var(--red);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.015);
      color:#c2c2c2;
      font-style:italic;
      white-space:pre-line;
      line-height:1.8;
      font-size:14px;
    }

    .evidence-grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr;
      gap:12px;
      margin-top:14px;
    }

    .evidence-card{
      background:#141414;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:14px;
      position:relative;
    }

    .evidence-card::after{
      content:"EVIDENCE";
      position:absolute;
      top:10px;
      right:12px;
      font-size:9px;
      color:#3b3b3b;
      letter-spacing:2px;
    }

    .evidence-title{
      color:var(--gold);
      font-size:12px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      letter-spacing:1px;
      margin-bottom:10px;
      padding-right:56px;
      line-height:1.5;
    }

    .profile{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr;
      gap:12px;
    }

    .profile-box{
      background:#141414;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:14px;
    }

    .small{
      color:#707070;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:8px;
    }

    .redacted{
      display:inline-block;
      background:#000;
      color:#000;
      border-radius:2px;
      padding:0 6px;
      user-select:none;
    }

    .note{
      margin-top:16px;
      background:#120d0d;
      border:1px solid #3a1d1d;
      padding:16px;
      position:relative;
    }

    .note::before{
      content:"Detective Note";
      position:absolute;
      top:-10px;
      left:10px;
      background:#120d0d;
      color:#d59696;
      padding:0 6px;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:1px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
    }

    .note p{
      color:#d8b5b5;
      margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    .objective{
      background:linear-gradient(180deg,#111,#151515);
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:15px;
      margin-top:8px;
    }

    .objective .head{
      color:var(--green);
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    ol{
      margin:0;
      padding-left:18px;
      color:#c3c3c3;
    }

    ol li{
      margin:8px 0;
      line-height:1.7;
      font-size:14px;
    }

    .final{
      margin-top:22px;
      border:1px solid #332222;
      background:#100c0c;
      padding:16px;
    }

    .final .head{
      color:#ffb3b3;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    .cta-wrap{
      margin-top:20px;
      text-align:center;
    }

    .cta{
      display:inline-block;
      width:100%;
      max-width:320px;
      text-align:center;
      text-decoration:none;
      background:transparent;
      border:1px solid var(--red);
      color:#e2b3b3;
      padding:14px 18px;
      font-size:13px;
      letter-spacing:2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      border-radius:6px;
      transition:transform .15s ease, background .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;
      box-shadow:0 0 0 rgba(0,0,0,0);
    }

    .cta:hover,
    .cta:focus{
      background:rgba(139,0,0,0.12);
      box-shadow:0 0 18px rgba(139,0,0,0.18);
      transform:translateY(-1px);
      outline:none;
    }

    .footer{
      border-top:1px solid #1c1c1c;
      background:#0c0c0c;
      padding:12px 16px;
      color:#484848;
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:1.2px;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      line-height:1.6;
    }

    @media (min-width:700px){
      body{
        padding:22px;
      }

      .content{
        padding:28px 22px 34px;
      }

      .header-grid{
        grid-template-columns:1.35fr .95fr;
        gap:18px;
        align-items:start;
      }

      .profile{
        grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
      }

      .evidence-grid{
        grid-template-columns:repeat(3, 1fr);
      }

      .title{
        font-size:30px;
      }

      .topmeta{
        font-size:12px;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width:420px){
      body{
        padding:8px;
      }

      .content{
        padding:18px 14px 24px;
      }

      .title{
        font-size:22px;
      }

      p,
      .list div,
      ol li,
      .quote{
        font-size:13px;
      }

      .file::before{
        display:none;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <article class="file">
    <div class="topbar">
      <span class="badge">Classified</span>
      <span class="topmeta">Case No. 0114-S | Theft / Suspected Homicide | Active Investigation</span>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="header-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="section-tag">Internal Affairs Division</div>
          <h1 class="title">Case File #114</h1>
          <div class="subtitle">Recovered archive — restricted circulation</div>
          <div class="stamp">Reopened</div>

          <p>
            This file concerns an incident previously dismissed due to insufficient evidence,
            incomplete witness testimony, and the absence of a confirmed body.
          </p>
          <p>
            New developments suggest the case was closed too early.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="meta-box">
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-label">Victim</span>
            <div class="meta-value">S.E.D</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-label">Condition</span>
            <div class="meta-value">Stable — psychologically compromised</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-label">Primary Incident Zone</span>
            <div class="meta-value">Maadi</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-label">Current Standing</span>
            <div class="meta-value">Active Investigation</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider">

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Section 01</div>
        <h2>Initial Report</h2>

        <p>
          Approximately one year ago, an unidentified male was discovered wandering near
          <strong>Maadi</strong> in a state of severe psychological distress.
        </p>

        <p>
          The subject was covered in blood.
          No visible external injuries were found.
        </p>

        <div class="list">
          <div>Surgical instruments recovered at scene</div>
          <div>Blood traces of unknown origin</div>
          <div>No confirmed body</div>
          <div>No identified secondary victim</div>
        </div>

        <p>During questioning, the subject repeated only fragmented statements:</p>

        <div class="quote">“They took it…”
“I couldn’t stop it…”
“She… she took everything…”</div>

        <p>
          With no witness, no body, and no corroborating evidence, the case was dismissed.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Until now.</strong></p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Section 02</div>
        <h2>Recent Developments</h2>

        <p>The same individual has resurfaced.</p>

        <div class="list">
          <div>Calm, controlled demeanor</div>
          <div>Deliberate emotional restraint</div>
          <div>Repeated attempts to initiate private “investments”</div>
          <div>Signs of selective memory recovery</div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Investigators believe the subject has regained partial control of the narrative.
        </p>

        <p><strong>But not the full truth.</strong></p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Section 03</div>
        <h2>Medical &amp; Psychological Notes</h2>

        <div class="list">
          <div>Persistent tremors in both hands</div>
          <div>Signs consistent with nicotine withdrawal</div>
          <div>Elevated emotional response under specific triggers</div>
          <div>Severe internal contradiction between memory and affect</div>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Critical Observation:</strong></p>

        <p>
          A wound was reported at the center of the chest.
        </p>

        <p>
          No incision.<br>
          No bruising.<br>
          No visible trauma.
        </p>

        <p>
          Yet the subject insists that <strong>something was removed</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          An engagement ring was later recovered from his right hand.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Evidence Archive</div>
        <h2>Evidence Log</h2>

        <div class="evidence-grid">
          <div class="evidence-card">
            <div class="evidence-title">Evidence #1 — Interrogation Fragment</div>
            <div class="quote">“I remember the moment…
I couldn’t breathe…
and then it was gone…

I didn’t lose it…

…she took it.”</div>
          </div>

          <div class="evidence-card">
            <div class="evidence-title">Evidence #2 — Sensory Trigger</div>
            <p>
              The subject reported a recurring sensory memory associated with the event:
            </p>
            <div class="quote">“It smelled like something… sweet… tropical… familiar…”</div>
          </div>

          <div class="evidence-card">
            <div class="evidence-title">Evidence #3 — Last Known Appearance</div>
            <div class="list">
              <div>Green sweater</div>
              <div>Blue jeans</div>
            </div>
            <p>
              This appearance is believed to be directly linked to the incident timeline.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Section 04</div>
        <h2>Working Theory</h2>

        <p>This does not appear to have been a random act.</p>

        <div class="list">
          <div>No struggle</div>
          <div>No defensive response</div>
          <div>No reported pursuit</div>
          <div>No attempt to reclaim what was taken</div>
        </div>

        <p>Which leads investigators to a critical hypothesis:</p>

        <div class="quote">The victim did not lose anything…
He allowed it to be taken.</div>

        <p>
          Whether this was consent, surrender, or emotional helplessness remains unknown.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Section 05</div>
        <h2>Suspect Profile</h2>

        <div class="profile">
          <div class="profile-box">
            <div class="small">Known Characteristics</div>
            <div class="list">
              <div>Female</div>
              <div>Personally known to the victim</div>
              <div>High emotional significance</div>
              <div>No known history of hostility</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="profile-box">
            <div class="small">Flagged Notes</div>
            <p>
              Influence level: <strong>severe</strong><br>
              Threat profile: <span class="redacted">REDACTED</span><br>
              Intent: unknown
            </p>
            <p>
              Most concerning detail:
              the suspect may be entirely unaware of the act.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="note">
          <p>This may not be a conventional theft.</p>
          <p>
            It is possible the victim is describing the removal of something emotional rather than physical.
          </p>
          <p>
            Translation: he may be calling it stolen only because he does not know how else to describe losing his heart.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-tag">Mission Directive</div>
        <h2>Detective Instruction</h2>

        <div class="objective">
          <div class="head">To proceed</div>
          <ol>
            <li>Identify the last confirmed physical trace</li>
            <li>Follow the sensory trigger</li>
            <li>Reconstruct the missing memory</li>
            <li>Determine whether the loss was taken… or willingly given</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="final">
        <div class="head">Final Note</div>
        <p>
          Be advised: this case may not lead you to a criminal.
        </p>
        <p>
          It may lead you to a truth the victim never wanted to confront.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some things are not stolen by force.
          Some are surrendered willingly…
          and only called theft after they are gone.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Proceed with caution, Detective.</strong></p>

        <div class="cta-wrap">
          <a class="cta" href="YOUR_LINK_HERE">Start Investigation</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      Case File #114 | Internal Affairs Division | Restricted
    </div>
  </article>
</body>
</html>
